snippet dfl "Generate a dict from a list" b
$1 = {
    $2
`!p
entries = t[2].split(' ')
entvar = entries[0]

snip.rv = ''
if len(entries) > 1:
    ovars = entries[1].split(",")
    for i, line in enumerate(ovars):
        snip += '    "{}": {}[{}],'.format(line, entvar, i)
    snip.rv += '\n' + snip.mkline(line='',indent=None)
`}
endsnippet

